• Clinical Query Pipeline: Architected and delivered a production end-to-end natural language processing pipeline that converts free-text clinical queries into structured intents, standardized medical concept identifiers (UMLS/SNOMED CT CUIs), retrieval signals, and topic groupings. The pipeline spans LLM-based intent extraction and query expansion (Gemini on Vertex AI), BigQuery-based concept summarization, hybrid retrieval using hierarchy-based, embedding-based, and graph-clustering methods, and a class-based service architecture with full production lifecycle management for enterprise deployment.

• Nature Breakdown API — Standardized Output Schema: Defined and enforced a standardized, versioned API output schema, replacing prompt-dependent formatting with Pydantic-based structural enforcement, pre-response validation, backward compatibility, versioning governance, and unit testing. The API has been deployed to the enterprise AI platform.

• Medical Knowledge Operations: Built BigQuery-driven concept clustering over UMLS relationship tables (MRCONSO, MRSTY, MRREL), producing deterministic cluster identifiers and per-concept knowledge lookups that support downstream retrieval and grounding.

• Clinical Query Context Taxonomy: Designed a versioned nine-context taxonomy that classifies clinical queries by their intended source of truth for routing and exclusion decisions, delivered in both stakeholder-facing and machine-readable formats.

